result.execSummary:
The defendant Tony Lee Tyra was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Filed, Letter Asking to Speak With Judge

Petitioner appeared, pro se.  City of Milwaukee and State of Wisconsin appear by Assistant District Attorney Sarah McNutt. 
Deputy Court Clerk: cmt
Hearing on petition of return of property proceeded.  Statements made by counsel and petitioner.  Court denies petition with prejudice.
Return of property hearing on June 23, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Tony Lee Tyra in court with attorney Kevin B. Dunn.  Elizabeth Longo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Matter before court for final pretrial.  Parties have reached a resolution and proceed with plea and sentencing. 
Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Sentencing proceeded. Statements by parties. 
Court sentences defendant to serve 3 days  in the House of Correction with credit for 3 days, a TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.  Court orders defendant to pay all costs, fees and surcharges by 11-05-2015 or civil judgment.  Appeal rights given. 

Filed: Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief and Pretrial Incarceration Credit
JusticePoint Pretrial Services Report received and filed.

Defendant Tony Lee Tyra in court with attorney Kevin B. Dunn.  Elizabeth Longo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Pretrial Services Violation Report Received.  Defendant has a positive breathalyzer test. Response to Violation Report - Court ordered that defendant meet with JusticePoint at least ONCE per week.  Court further orders that defendant get involved with some form of alcohol/drug treatment forthwith.  Court reminds defendant that further positive tests may result in modification of bail.  Case remains set for 5-5-2015 final pretrial in Branch 46. jks

Defendant Tony Lee Tyra in court with attorney Kevin B. Dunn.  Elizabeth Longo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Court ordered case adjourned for final pre-trial conference and jury trial in Branch 46. jks

Defendant Tony Lee Tyra in court with attorney Kevin B. Dunn.  Sarah McNutt appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defense requests a status date to discuss the evidence and decide whether they want to resolve the case or proceed to trial.   Court ordered case adjourned for status conference in Branch 46. jks
  Status conference scheduled for 03-02-2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Tony Lee Tyra in court with attorney Kevin B. Dunn.  Alyssa M. Schaller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Request for substitution made by defense counsel.  Court consented to substitution against Judge John Siefert, Branch 47.  Defendant is advised the Clerk of Circuit Court reassigned case, pursuant to current court rules, to  Judge Reserve , Branch 46.  Case adjourned to Branch 46 for status conference.  Status conference scheduled for 02-06-2015 at 08:30 am.

Court orders defendant TURNED OVER to JUSTICE Point for Supervision.  
ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY/DEFENDANT to be monitored by drug testing and portable breathalyzers.    
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Tony Lee Tyra in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Defendant Tony Lee Tyra in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Siefert, Branch 47.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for January 20, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
